Banks Are FTSE 100’s Biggest Tax Haven Users, Telegraph Says

-- B y   C h r i s   P e t e r s o n
-- 
2011-10-11T05:15:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-11/banks-are-ftse-100-s-biggest-tax-haven-users-telegraph-says.html
U.K. banks are the biggest users of
 tax havens  in the FTSE-100, the Daily Telegraph reported, citing
a survey by the charity ActionAid.  HSBC Holdings Plc (HSBA) , Royal Bank of Scotland Plc,  Barclays Plc (BARC) 
and  Lloyds Banking Group Plc (LLOY)  operate 1,649 companies in low-tax
territories such as the island of Jersey and the Cayman Islands;
 WPP Plc (WPP) , the world’s largest advertising company, has 2,686
companies and an unidentified spokesman said WPP had a duty to
shareholders to plan its tax arrangements, the newspaper said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Chris Peterson at 
 cpeterson@bloomberg.net  